summary:
I work as a Platform Engineer at IKEA, Delft (Netherlands), and am excited to continue pursuing the dream of creating a better everyday life for many people together.

My strengths are in Microsoft Azure Administration, Azure DevOps, Microsoft Power BI, Ambari and Hadoop Administration, Azure Databricks, Nifi Administration, Infrastructure as Code, SAP Business Objects (BO) BI, Alteryx, Microsoft Azure, 360Suite GB&Smith, Jenkins, JIRA, Bitbucket, etc. I have also provided solutions and support for reports, applications, technologies, operating systems, and modules, and resolved issues related to installation/update/content migration/object promotion, etc. My interests in this subject range from fault tolerance, adaptability, and swarming.

In the past, I worked with Avanade B.V. Netherlands as Consultant and helped one of the biggest financial clients to achieve a transformation in data and analytics. Before that was with Infosys for 5 years as Senior Associate Consultant for multiple global projects including on-site assignments in New Zealand and the Netherlands and also with KPIT Technologies for 3 Years as a Support Engineer for SAP in Germany.

I hold a Bachelor of Engineering Degree in Computer Science from an affiliated University with RGTU.
Contrary to the professional front, I like to travel and have a keen interest in organizing various events and cultural activities in Amsterdam.
